- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper uses a multilinear spectral method for partitioning the tensor representation of higher-order network structures. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the implementation of the proposed algorithm. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also less likely but possible as the paper mentions the use of the proposed algorithm for graph anomaly detection, which can be related to neural network-based anomaly detection methods.
